{"word":"G1271 - διάνοια - diánoia - dee-an'-oy-ah - Imagination","slug":"G1271","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">διάνοια</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>diánoia"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>dee-an'-oy-ah"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Imagination"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"- Original: <b><el>διάνοια</el></b> <p />- Transliteration: <b>Dianoia</b> <p />- Phonetic: <b>dee-an'-oy-ah</b> <p class=\"def\">- Definition: </p> <p class='li260'><b>1.</b> the mind as a faculty of understanding, feeling, desiring </p> <p class='li260'><b>2.</b> understanding </p> <p class='li260'><b>3.</b> mind, i.e. spirit, way of thinking and feeling </p> <p class='li260'><b>4.</b> thoughts, either good or bad </p> <p class=\"origin\"/>- Origin: from <a href=\"#/G1223\">G1223</a> and <a href=\"#/G3563\">G3563</a> <p />- TDNT entry: 20:03,6 <p />- Part(s) of speech: Noun Feminine <p />- Strong's: From <a href=\"#/G1223\">G1223</a> and <a href=\"#/G3563\">G3563</a>; <i>deep thought</i> properly the faculty (<i>mind</i> or its <i>disposition</i>) by implication its <b>exercise</b>: - imagination mind understanding. "},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/G1270\">G1270</a>, <a href=\"#/G1425\">G1425</a>, <a href=\"#/G1771\">G1771</a>, <a href=\"#/G2132\">G2132</a>, <a href=\"#/G2133\">G2133</a>, <a href=\"#/G2657\">G2657</a>, <a href=\"#/G279\">G279</a>, <a href=\"#/G3340\">G3340</a>, <a href=\"#/G3539\">G3539</a>, <a href=\"#/G3540\">G3540</a>, <a href=\"#/G3559\">G3559</a>, <a href=\"#/G3563\">G3563</a>, <a href=\"#/G4306\">G4306</a>, <a href=\"#/G4307\">G4307</a>, <a href=\"#/G453\">G453</a>, <a href=\"#/G454\">G454</a>, <a href=\"#/G5282\">G5282</a>, <a href=\"#/G5283\">G5283</a>"}]}